cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about a language model that combines recurrent neural networks to generate both word tokens and letters in each word type. It focuses on natural language processing and machine learning, which are covered by the Computer Science sub-categories cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of embeddings, which are a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the model's ability to generate spellings for novel words in context suggests a potential application in neural machine translation (cs.NE) or computer vision (cs.CV) tasks.
